I have created an operational Python script which computes one's body mass index (BMI) to keep track of physical well-being. In connection with the completion of my certificate in Python, I thought that my acquired knowledge about mathematical operations and conditional statements could be used in practice.

This program allows the user to enter their weight measured in kilograms and height measured in meters, and compute his/her BMI using the formula and determine the category he/she falls under using 'if-elif-else' statements: whether it is 'Underweight', 'Normal' or 'Overweight'. While developing this program, I made sure to create an easy-to-use interface for the user as well as make sure that all mathematical calculations would be correct.

